{"comments":"Frames — Frame count atom for frame-based animation timing.\n\nRepresents discrete frame counts for animation and video work.\nUsed in motion graphics, video editing, and game loop timing.\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nFrames are the atomic unit of discrete time in visual media.\nUnlike continuous time (seconds, milliseconds), frames are always\nintegers — you cannot have half a frame.\n\nCombined with FPS, frames convert to/from wall-clock time.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","Frames"],"Frames"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[64,38],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/Frames.purs","start":[64,1]},"title":"eqFrames"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","Frames"],"Frames"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[65,40],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/Frames.purs","start":[65,1]},"title":"ordFrames"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","Frames"],"Frames"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[68,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/Frames.purs","start":[67,1]},"title":"showFrames"}],"comments":"Frame count (0 or greater)\n\nBounded by construction. Negative frame counts cannot exist.\nNo upper bound — animations can be arbitrarily long.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data"